# Accessibility Standards (WCAG)

## ARIA Attributes

Always add proper ARIA labels to interactive elements:

```tsx
<Toggle aria-label="Bold text" aria-pressed={isBold} title="Bold (Ctrl+B)">
  <Bold className="size-4" aria-hidden="true" />
</Toggle>
```

## Keyboard Navigation

- All functionality must be accessible via keyboard
- Use standard shortcuts: Ctrl+B, Ctrl+I, Ctrl+U, etc.
- Ensure focus indicators are visible
- Use tabIndex appropriately

## Screen Readers

- Add descriptive aria-label to icon-only buttons
- Use aria-hidden="true" for decorative icons
- Provide alternative text for images
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Focus Management

- Auto-focus editor on mount (configurable)
- Return focus to editor after dialog closes
- Manage focus in floating toolbars

## Color Contrast

- Ensure sufficient contrast for text
- Don't rely solely on color to convey information
- Support dark mode
